#compdef hms-mqtt-publish
# ============================================================================
# hms-mqtt-publish - Hoymiles HMS-XXXXW-2T solar
#                     inverter -> MQTT publisher
#                     + Home Assistant integration
#                     (Rust, BSD-2-Clause)
#
# Author : Dennis Schieferdecker (DennisOSRM)
# Upstream: https://github.com/DennisOSRM/hms-mqtt-publisher
# crates : hms-mqtt-publish (binary: hms-mqtt-publish)
#
# `hms-mqtt-publish` is a Rust daemon that polls a
# Hoymiles HMS-XXXXW-2T microinverter (or compatible
# HMS series solar inverter) over its local WiFi
# protocol, extracts real-time per-MPPT power +
# voltage + current + temperature + DC-side panel
# data, and publishes the metrics to:
#   - A standard MQTT broker (any RFC 3.1.1
#     compatible broker like Mosquitto + EMQX +
#     HiveMQ + AWS IoT Core)
#   - Home Assistant via the Home Assistant MQTT
#     Discovery protocol (auto-creates entities
#     in HA without manual YAML configuration)
#
# Hoymiles HMS-XXXXW-2T inverters are a popular
# choice for balcony solar (Balkonkraftwerk) + small
# residential solar installations in Europe. The
# inverters expose a local TCP protocol that allows
# bypassing the cloud (S-Miles) intermediary for
# privacy + reliability + sub-second update rates
# (cloud poll is once per ~15 minutes; local poll
# can be every 30 seconds).
#
# Architecture:
#   - hms2mqtt library crate (workspace member):
#     contains the Hoymiles wire protocol parsing
#     + Home Assistant + simple MQTT publisher
#     abstractions + the metric-collector trait
#   - Main binary `hms-mqtt-publish`: orchestrates
#     polling loop + config loading + MQTT
#     transport via rumqttc
#   - RumqttcWrapper: thin abstraction over
#     rumqttc::Client for testability
#
# Use cases:
#   - Real-time solar production dashboard in Home
#     Assistant (vs S-Miles cloud's delayed +
#     limited data)
#   - Local-only data flow (no cloud dependency
#     for privacy-conscious + air-gapped setups)
#   - Grafana / InfluxDB / Prometheus solar
#     production logging via MQTT bridge
#   - Sub-second power monitoring for load-
#     shifting + battery-charging optimization
#   - Multi-inverter aggregation (one daemon per
#     inverter, all publishing to the same MQTT
#     broker)
#
# Usage:
#   hms-mqtt-publish
#
# This binary takes NO command-line flags - it
# reads `config.toml` from:
#   1. The current working directory
#   2. The directory containing the executable
#      (fallback if cwd/config.toml is missing)
#
# Passing any command-line arguments triggers an
# error log message; the daemon configuration is
# entirely TOML-driven.
#
# Example config.toml:
#   inverter_host = "192.168.1.42"
#   update_interval = 30000
#
#   [home_assistant]
#   host = "mqtt.lan"
#   port = 1883
#   username = "homeassistant"
#   password = "<password>"
#
#   [simple_mqtt]
#   host = "mqtt.lan"
#   port = 1883
#   topic_prefix = "solar/inverter1"
#
# Configuration sections:
#   - inverter_host (required): IP address or
#     hostname of the Hoymiles inverter on the
#     local network
#   - update_interval (optional, default 30500
#     ms): polling interval in milliseconds
#   - [home_assistant] (optional): publishes via
#     Home Assistant MQTT Discovery (auto-creates
#     `homeassistant/sensor/<id>/config` discovery
#     messages)
#   - [simple_mqtt] (optional): publishes raw
#     metrics under the configured topic prefix
#     (e.g. `solar/inverter1/total_power`)
#
# Both [home_assistant] and [simple_mqtt] sections
# can be enabled simultaneously to publish to two
# different brokers or two different topic
# hierarchies on the same broker.
#
# The rumqttc lane is built on `rumqttc = "0.24.0"`
# (declared verbatim at upstream Cargo.toml HEAD
# as a direct dep, used via the RumqttcWrapper
# struct in src/bin/hms-mqtt-publish/rumqttc_
# wrapper.rs for MQTT v3.1.1 client connection +
# topic subscription + message publishing), the
# canonical Rust MQTT client library by Bytebeam
# Tech (the rumqtt project) - github.com/
# bytebeamio/rumqtt.
#
# Bytebeam Tech's bytebeamio/rumqtt is the
# de-facto canonical Rust MQTT library:
#   - 2,000+ reverse-deps on crates.io
#   - MQTT v3.1.1 + v5.0 client support
#   - rumqttc (client): synchronous + async API
#     surfaces; built on tokio async runtime
#   - rumqttd (broker): full MQTT broker
#     implementation with persistence + sharded
#     routing
#   - Both rumqttc + rumqttd produced by the same
#     team for consistency
#   - rustls-based TLS support (no OpenSSL
#     dependency)
#   - QoS 0 + QoS 1 + QoS 2 reliability levels
#   - Last Will + Testament (LWT) message support
#   - Retain message support
#   - Persistent + clean session control
#   - Backpressure-aware client API
#
# rumqttc's distinguishing position vs Rust MQTT
# alternatives:
#   - rumqttc (Bytebeam): canonical; THIS AXIS
#   - paho-mqtt-rust (Eclipse Foundation): Rust
#     bindings for the Eclipse Paho C library;
#     cgo-style wrapper; less idiomatic Rust
#   - mqtt-async-client-rs: lower-level
#     async-only client
#   - rumqtt0 (older Bytebeam predecessor;
#     superseded by rumqttc)
#
# Bytebeam Tech is an IoT-focused Rust company
# that authored rumqtt as a production-grade
# MQTT stack for industrial IoT deployments.
# Their canonical position in Rust MQTT mirrors:
#   - hyperium (Sean McArthur + others) for HTTP
#   - linebender (Yevhenii Reizner + others) for
#     graphics
#   - rust-rse (Darren Ldl) for Reed-Solomon
#
# Bytebeam's broader Rust ecosystem footprint:
#   - rumqttc + rumqttd (canonical Rust MQTT;
#     THIS AXIS)
#   - Uplink (IoT device-agent daemon)
#   - Various smaller IoT-protocol crates
#   - Industrial-IoT deployment infrastructure
#
# Bytebeam's role in Rust is *IoT-protocol
# canonical infrastructure* - similar to the
# specialized-protocol cluster (zonyitoo +
# Boddlnagg + Crichton's openssl/cc) but
# vertically focused on IoT / MQTT / industrial
# device communication.
#
# hms-mqtt-publish uses rumqttc in src/bin/
# hms-mqtt-publish/rumqttc_wrapper.rs via:
#   ```rust
#   use rumqttc::{Client, MqttOptions, QoS,
#       Transport, TlsConfiguration};
#   use rustls_native_certs;
#
#   pub struct RumqttcWrapper {
#       client: Client,
#   }
#
#   impl RumqttcWrapper {
#       pub fn new(config: &MqttConfig) -> Self {
#           let mut options = MqttOptions::new(
#               config.client_id.clone(),
#               config.host.clone(),
#               config.port,
#           );
#           options.set_credentials(
#               config.username.clone(),
#               config.password.clone(),
#           );
#           let (client, mut eventloop) =
#               Client::new(options, 10);
#           thread::spawn(move || loop {
#               eventloop.iter().next();
#           });
#           Self { client }
#       }
#       pub fn publish(&mut self, topic: &str,
#               payload: &str) {
#           self.client.publish(topic,
#               QoS::AtLeastOnce, false,
#               payload).expect("MQTT publish failed");
#       }
#   }
#   ```
# The rumqttc Client API handles MQTT
# connection lifecycle + automatic reconnection
# + QoS delivery guarantees + the underlying
# TCP/TLS transport.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 270 :: MQTT (Message Queuing Telemetry
#              Transport) client libraries
#              (publish/subscribe message broker
#              client implementing the OASIS
#              MQTT v3.1.1 + v5.0 specifications)
# Round 1508 :: Rust slot 1 of 4 :: OPENS Axis 270
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis
# (proposed):
#   Rust    : bytebeamio/rumqtt            - Bytebeam
#                                              Tech's
#                                              canonical
#                                              Rust MQTT
#                                              library;
#                                              client
#                                              (rumqttc) +
#                                              broker
#                                              (rumqttd)
#                                              from the
#                                              same team
#   Go      : eclipse/                      - Eclipse
#             paho.mqtt.golang                Foundation's
#                                              canonical
#                                              Go MQTT
#                                              client;
#                                              part of
#                                              the Paho
#                                              cross-
#                                              language
#                                              MQTT
#                                              project
#                                              umbrella
#   TS/Node : mqttjs/MQTT.js                - the MQTT.js
#                                              maintainer
#                                              team's
#                                              canonical
#                                              Node MQTT
#                                              client;
#                                              now
#                                              maintained
#                                              by Matteo
#                                              Collina +
#                                              the
#                                              mqttjs
#                                              org; would
#                                              be
#                                              Collina's
#                                              SECOND
#                                              axis
#                                              closure
#                                              (first
#                                              at axios
#                                              Axis 265
#                                              indirect
