#
# MQTT is a *spec-bound* axis - the OASIS MQTT
# v3.1.1 specification (Oct 2014) + v5.0
# specification (Mar 2019) define the binary
# wire protocol byte-for-byte:
#   - CONNECT / CONNACK handshake
#   - PUBLISH (QoS 0/1/2) message types
#   - SUBSCRIBE / SUBACK / UNSUBSCRIBE /
#     UNSUBACK
#   - PINGREQ / PINGRESP keepalive
#   - DISCONNECT
#   - AUTH (v5.0 only)
#
# Compliant implementations interoperate at the
# wire-protocol level - the same MQTT broker
# can serve clients written in any language
# using any canonical library.
#
# Structural commentary on the canonical libraries:
#   - rumqttc (Rust): pure-Rust client + broker
#     from the same team; production-grade
#     IoT-focused implementation
#   - paho.mqtt.golang (Go): part of the
#     Eclipse Paho cross-language project;
#     uses cgo-free pure-Go networking
#   - MQTT.js (Node): isomorphic browser + Node;
#     WebSocket + TCP + TLS support; the most-
#     installed Node MQTT client by far
#
# Cross-language interop at the MQTT wire-
# protocol level - all three libraries can
# connect to + publish/subscribe via the same
# broker (Mosquitto + EMQX + HiveMQ + AWS IoT
# Core + Azure IoT Hub + Google Cloud IoT).
#
# Axis 270 opens with the Rust slot at
# Bytebeam's rumqttc, anchoring their canonical
# position in Rust IoT-protocol infrastructure.
# Subsequent rounds will visit the Go (eclipse/
# paho.mqtt.golang) + TS/Node (mqttjs/MQTT.js)
# canonicals.
#
# MQTT is the dominant IoT messaging protocol:
#   - Used by Home Assistant + OpenHAB +
#     Domoticz + ESPHome + Tasmota for smart-
#     home device communication
#   - Used by AWS IoT Core + Azure IoT Hub +
#     Google Cloud IoT Core for cloud-IoT
#     integration
#   - Used by industrial SCADA + manufacturing
#     telemetry systems
#   - Used by automotive + fleet-management
#     telematics
#   - Used by ship-tracking + airline tracking
#     + environmental sensor networks
#
# Use case spectrum for this axis:
#   - hms-mqtt-publish (Rust, rumqttc): Hoymiles
#     solar inverter -> MQTT publisher for Home
#     Assistant integration
# ============================================================================

_hms-mqtt-publish() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]' \
        '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[print version]'
}

_hms-mqtt-publish "$@"
